	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "According to her hagiography she was a daughter of Decius, high priest of the gods of the city of Antioch and emperor (?), but was raised as a Christian by her nurse.\n                  She was martyred after she rejected the advances of a Roman governor. Not to be confused with Marinā commemorated on 15 Nāḥase.\n             " .
